properties.abstract: A scenic hike through the wildest valley in the Lake Maggiore region. Enjoy the Onsernone Valley's tranquillity on old paths. Dense forests, waterfalls and hidden rustici line the route. The views extend over the deep valleys to Lake Maggiore.
properties.description:
Three hundred bends lead up to Spruga, the last village of the Onsernone Valley at an altitude of 1,100 metres. The picturesque Ticino village sits on a sunny terrace above the deep gorge of the Isorno river. The valley has retained its original character with its rustic stone houses, high-altitude alps, steep paths and primaeval forests.

From Spruga, the steep trail winds its way up to Al Pianscc. Continue on the old path under shady larch trees to Alpe Pescd. After another 200 metres in altitude difference, you cross the hike's highest point and reach the Munzzelmm massif. The scenic mountain trail leads past the Laghtt di Sali mountain lake, where you can cool off on hot summer days. Shortly afterwards, you come to Alpe Sali and the hut of the same name. The Capanna Sali sits surrounded by expansive meadows, where black grouse mate in spring and cows graze in summer. The sunny terrace is well worth a break. The panoramic views stretch to Lake Maggiore. Those who prefer to do without the 1,100-metre ascent can reach the hut by cable car from Vergeletto.

At the Capanna Sali begins a 30-minute climb to Pizzo Zucchero. The trail ascends gently at first and then gets steeper. The summit offers views over the Valle di Vergeletto and the Valle Onsernone to the Magadino plain. In good visibility, you can see the Monte Rosa massif in the distance. The Swing the World makes the views twice as delightful.

The return to the hut follows the ascent route. The trail then branches off to the left and leads through the enchanting Val Lavadina, past the sun-kissed hamlet of Lig'nc to Comologno. The last section down to the village once again includes many steps.
